<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676776>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Head scalation of Lioscincus s.s. as seen inL. steindachneri (adapted from Sadlier, 1987) showing some of the primary diagnostic features for the genus including fused frontoparietal scales (FP), a narrow-based and semilunar anterior loreal scale (AL) which contacts the upper labial scales narrowly or not at all, and divided nuchal scales (N), compared to the plesiomorphic condition of a broad-based anterior loreal and single transversely elongate nuchal either side of the neck as seen in Epibator (Fig. 4), Phasmasaurus (Fig. 5) and Caesoris novaecaledoniae (Fig. 7), and paired frontoparietals seen in Epibator (Fig. 4)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4676776/files/figure.png" .

